::xowiki::Page new \
	-set name en:reference_kv_question.page \
	-title "Question Command Reference" \
	-text {
<p><u>Name:</u></p>
<p>question - Create a question element</p>

<p><u>Synopsis:</u></p>
<p><b>question</b> <i>identifier</i> key <i>value</i></p>

<p><u>Description:</u></p>
<p>Creates a question element based on key-value pairs. The provided <i>identifier</i> is used as an id for the element in order to reference it (e.g.: q1 or topic_A). A question can be of type singleChoice or mulitpleChoice.</p>

<p>The keys title, question and feedback receive simple text input. Answers are set via the answer key in the form of a list where each list item consists of the structure "Answer text", [correct|wrong].</p>

<p>Valid keys are:</p>

<p><b>question</b> <i>identifier</i> <b>title</b> question_title<br>
<b>question</b> <i>identifier</i> <b>type</b> [singleChoice|multipleChoice]<br>
<b>question</b> <i>identifier</i> <b>question</b> question_text<br>
<b>question</b> <i>identifier</i> <b>answers</b> (answer_text, [correct|wrong], ?...?)<br>
<b>question</b> <i>identifier</i> <b>feedback</b> feedback_text</p>

<p><u>Example:</u></p>
<code class="example">question q1 title "Question Example"<br>
question q1 type singleChoice<br>
question q1 question "Select the answer which is correct."<br>
question q1 answers ("Sample answer text", wrong, "Another text", true)<br>
question q1 feedback "This field can provide additional feedback"</code>
} \
	-description {Question}
